---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PriceTag from "../components/PriceTag.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Adidas Samba | Market Pricing"
  description="Dedicated page for Adidas Samba pricing and value-based positioning."
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="section-kicker mb-3">Section 02</p>
    <h1 class="section-title mb-4">Market Pricing</h1>
    <p class="muted-copy max-w-3xl">
      This page isolates the pricing conversation: where the current range comes from,
      why consumers accept it, and what supports a premium over generic alternatives.
    </p>
  </section>

  <PriceTag />

  <section class="section-shell pb-20">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <article class="glass-card p-6">
        <p class="section-kicker mb-2">Signal</p>
        <h3 class="panel-title">Brand Equity</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Brand memory and recognizability allow Adidas to protect margins in a crowded segment.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="glass-card p-6">
        <p class="section-kicker mb-2">Market force</p>
        <h3 class="panel-title">Trend-Led Demand</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Social media momentum increases perceived scarcity and strengthens willingness to pay.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="glass-card p-6">
        <p class="section-kicker mb-2">Constraint</p>
        <h3 class="panel-title">Substitutes Exist</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Competitors limit pricing power, but product differentiation prevents perfect substitution.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
